title: Microsoft reveals Pluton, a custom security chip built into Intel, AMD, and Qualcomm processors

text: Microsoft is announcing a new, security-focused computer chip that it says will make laptops more secure as many corporate workers never plan to return to an office full-time.  On Tuesday the software giant announced the new Pluton Processor, which will be put into Microsoft Windows computer chips by AMD, Intel, and Qualcomm and will ship in devices in the next three years.
